You need to reverse a given string without using any built-in reverse method. How would you approach this task?

Answer: To reverse a string without using any built-in reverse method, you can convert the string to a character array and swap the characters from the beginning and end of the array. Hereâ€™s an example code snippet:

public class ReverseString {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "Hello, World!";
        char[] characters = input.toCharArray();

        int start = 0;
        int end = characters.length - 1;

        while (start < end) {
            char temp = characters[start];
            characters[start] = characters[end];
            characters[end] = temp;

            start++;
            end--;
        }
        String reversedString = new String(characters);
        System.out.println(reversedString);

    }
}
